commit.message: Bump version to 0.1.7
Use Symbola font to improve emoji support in PDFs
Fix gemojione link in the documentation
Bump version to 0.1.6
Bumped the minimum required Sphinx version to 1.8
Replaced calls to deprecated Sphinx methods with the new versions.
merge two sections made separate by accident during rebase

use more descriptive link name

Addressing a review comment https://github.com/sphinx-contrib/emojicodes/pull/12#discussion_r396013077

"In the new version of the documentation, I'm including the README inside
the index.rst. That's why I've changed the wording. When the link is
rendered on GitHub or PyPI, the wording "the project's documentation page"
makes sense, but when it's rendered as part of the docs, it reads strange.

I like more descriptive links, but in this case I compromised on "here"
for the above reasons. Nevertheless, I'll change it to "the project's
documentation page" and we can improve it later if we can think
of something better."

improve docs: include index, add info about styles

Fixes https://github.com/sphinx-contrib/emojicodes/issues/11
Bump version to 0.1.5
Update documentation
Add Joypixels codes and make them the default
Do not remove old emoji codes from the list
